CONFIGURE.FZ
============

configure.fz is ForgeZero's lightweight build-script language. It is evaluated
during configuration and can mutate the active build context before the main
build graph is created.

BASIC EXAMPLE
-------------
ctx.AddSources("src/**/*.c")
ctx.AddCompilerFlags("-DDEBUG")
ctx.AddLDFlags("-Wl,--gc-sections")

AVAILABLE OPERATIONS
---------------------
ctx.AddSources(pattern)
ctx.RemoveSources(pattern)
ctx.AddCompilerFlags(flag)
ctx.RemoveCompilerFlags(flag)
ctx.AddLDFlags(flag)
ctx.RemoveLDFlags(flag)
ctx.SetVariable(name, value)

NOTES
-----
The script runs with access to the current environment and the resolved config
values. This makes it suitable for platform checks, toolchain detection,
generated-source discovery, and build-profile specialization.
